<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-05-12T20:48:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-05-12T20:48:00-05:00" n="901" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d901">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">715.16/21: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Consul in Chargé of the Legation in
                                Honduras</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Lawton</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tegucigalpa</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-05-12T20:00:00-05:48"><hi rend="italic">May 12,
                                        1920—8 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received May 13—3:18
                                p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>41. Hondurean Government has received an ultimatum from the Salvadorean
                            Government which arrived after the time of grace had passed and
                            Hondurean Minister Resident in Salvador also reports that General Leiva
                            started to-day to invade Honduras with arms supplied by the Salvadorean
                            Government. …</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Lawton</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>